Add a Question Order Field as an Extension  to the Questionnaire Resource 
Purpose: To display Questions on the User Interface as per the ingested numerical order (i.e. 1st, 2nd....) from a FHIR database.
Explanation: In the Base Questionnaire Resource, there is no field that maintains the order of the questions (as received from the FHIR database) to be displayed on the User Interface. The proposed extension will persist the data (i.e. Item) in the same order it was received from the external entities (for example: from the Assessment Centre or from a Lime Survey database - via an API). This is because, if we do not maintain the order of the questions as received from the external entities, the default is to consider the first row persisted in the database as the first question and then display it accordingly. This might not always be the case.

Make the “Questionnaire” Resource to be Mandatorily Associated  with the “QuestionnaireResponse” Resource
Purpose: To associate a specific question item in the Questionnaire Resource with the associated response captured in the QuestionnaireResponse Resource.
Explanation: Since QuestionnaireResponse captures the responses to questions present in a Questionnaire, it would increase the efficiency of matching Question items to their associated QuestionnaireResponse values if it was mandatory to include the Questionnaire identifier with the QuestionnaireResponse.

Add "Title" as a New Parameter for the Search Functionality
Purpose: To ease the search for a given Measure from the available Measures in a FHIR server.
Explanation: We have identified one more Parameter (i.e. “Title” - referring to a Keyword in the title of the Survey/Measure) on which we will implement Search Functionality along with the other two in-scope parameters (i.e. Identifier and version) for the Questionnaire Resource. This is because it is more intuitive for a human to perform a word search rather than to search for a numerical identifier. To apply this search functionality, the FHIR server would receive a request to render different Questionnaires by Title as follows:                                      http://00.00.00.00:0000/lphi-fhir-server/api/Questionnaire?tite=Function; http://00.00.00.00:0000/lphi-fhir-server/api/Questionnaire?tite=Physical; http://00.00.00.00:0000/lphi-fhir-server/api/Questionnaire?tite=PACIC; http://00.00.00.00:0000/lphi-fhir-server/api/Questionnaire?tite=Physical Function Pro v2.0; In this case, the 00.00.00.00 = example IP address of the server and 0000 = example port number for the receiving server and the title = the word search performed by the user.
